## How to Handle Common Scenarios

### Scenario: Client slow to provide credentials

**Update dashboard:**
- Status: Waiting on Client
- Blocker: "Waiting for DNS access since Jan 15"
- Next Action: "Follow up with client"
- Add note: "Sent reminder Jan 17, Jan 19. If no response by Jan 22, will escalate."

**In your Monday update, highlight:**
"‚ö†Ô∏è Resend Email integration is blocked waiting for DNS access (requested Jan 15). Without this, we can't test email features scheduled for Week 3. Can you provide by Jan 22?"

### Scenario: Integration failed testing

**Update dashboard:**
- Status: Blocked
- Blocker: "OAuth returns 400 error in staging"
- Next Action: "Debug redirect URL configuration"
- Add note: "Works in dev, fails in staging. Checking environment credentials."

**Don't mark Complete until tested in all environments**

### Scenario: Integration taking longer than expected

**Update dashboard:**
- Keep status accurate (In Progress)
- Update Target Date to realistic date
- Add note explaining delay
- Blocker: "Google OAuth approval taking longer than expected (submitted Jan 15, usually 1-3 days)"

**In Monday update:**
"üü° Google SSO delayed - OAuth approval taking longer than typical 1-3 days. Will follow up with Google. Backup plan: Launch with email login, add Google login in v1.1."

---

## Integration Checklist (Copy This Into Your Dashboard)

Use this to ensure nothing is missed:

### Email Integration (Resend, SendGrid, etc.)

- [ ] Account created
- [ ] Domain added to service
- [ ] DNS records provided to client
- [ ] DNS records added by client
- [ ] Domain verified (wait 24-48hrs)
- [ ] Test email sent successfully
- [ ] Checked spam folder
- [ ] API key generated
- [ ] API key added to all environments (dev/staging/prod)
- [ ] Email templates configured
- [ ] Tested in staging
- [ ] Tested in production

### Google SSO

- [ ] Google Cloud Console account created
- [ ] OAuth consent screen configured
- [ ] Privacy policy URL added
- [ ] Redirect URLs added (all environments)
- [ ] SHA-1 keys generated (Android)
- [ ] SHA-1 keys added to Firebase
- [ ] OAuth app submitted for verification
- [ ] OAuth app approved
- [ ] Tested in dev environment
- [ ] Tested in staging environment
- [ ] Tested in production
- [ ] Tested on both iOS and Android

### Database (Supabase, Firebase, etc.)

- [ ] Account created
- [ ] Project created
- [ ] Database schema designed
- [ ] Schema reviewed with client
- [ ] Tables created
- [ ] Row Level Security policies configured
- [ ] API keys generated
- [ ] API keys added to environments
- [ ] Test data inserted
- [ ] Dev can read/write data
- [ ] Tested in staging
- [ ] Production database set up separately
- [ ] Backup strategy configured

