## Tips for Keeping This Updated

**Make it a Monday ritual:**
- Block 15 minutes every Monday morning
- Go through each integration
- Update status based on what happened last week
- Send client update immediately after

**Use it in daily standups:**
- "Let me check the integration dashboard..."
- Reference it when dev says "blocked"
- Update it live during standup

**Share it proactively:**
- Don't wait for client to ask "what's the status?"
- Send weekly without being asked
- Shows you're organized and on top of things

**Keep notes detailed:**
- Future you will thank present you
- "Waiting on client" is not helpful 3 weeks later
- "Waiting on client to provide DNS access - emailed Jan 15, followed up Jan 17" is helpful

---

## Success Metrics

**Dashboard is working if:**
- ‚úÖ Client knows status without asking
- ‚úÖ Dev knows what's blocking them
- ‚úÖ You can answer "what's the status?" in 30 seconds
- ‚úÖ No surprises on launch day (everything tracked)

**Dashboard needs improvement if:**
- ‚ùå Client constantly asking for updates (not checking dashboard)
- ‚ùå Statuses are outdated (not updating regularly)
- ‚ùå Too many items in "Blocked" with no action plan
- ‚ùå Completing items without testing in all environments
